result.execSummary:
The defendant Gabino Castaneda was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: With Huber privileges consistent with the rules of the jail while the inmate maintains a minimum security status. The defendant, at the discretion of the Sheriff, may perform community service work as an inmate worker in the county jail and shall earn statutory good time for same.

miscConds.notes:
Bond amount posted shall be applied.  If probation is revoked or will discharge with outstanding financial obligations due, a civil judgment shall be entered for the balance due. 

Defendant shall provide a biological specimen for DNA analysis.  Defendant has the right to request expungement of DNA analysis in writing through the Department of Justice. 

Defendant shall reimburse the Clerk of Courts for attorney fees as previously ordered or judgment shall be entered.

Defendant shall maintain absolute sobriety. 

Defendant shall have no contact with Collin's Deck Bar.
Defendant shall undergo an AODA assessment and comply with recommendations.

Defendant shall participate in all counseling, assessments, and/or treatment programs directed by the probation agent and comply with recommendations.

Defendant shall undergo a Mental Health Evaluation and comply with treatment recommendations.
